<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6255d20e-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1490"><num value="1490">§ 1490.</num><heading> Maturity of loans</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The maturity of any loan guaranteed or insured hereunder shall not exceed thirty years.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6255d20f-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/93/262/tII/s210">Pub. L. 93–262, title II, § 210</ref>, <date date="1974-04-12">Apr. 12, 1974</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/80">88 Stat. 80</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
